@DataBase BBSPrompt_Commands.guide

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node SysopCommands "Sysop Commands"

  Sysop Commands
  ==============

    Here's a list of the commands that can be used when you use the example
    configuration files are used, all these commands are completly
    configurable.

    Door Name          Details
    ================== =======================================================
    Accounts           This is a very basic account editor, for use by
                       co-sysops and other privelidged users.

                       It is used to edit other users accounts, validate
                       new users and remove users and their access settings.

    CallersLog         This simple door lets you view the callers log,  you
                       may also search for text in it, as well as looking at
                       what a user dir when they were on-line.

    Shell              Access the operating system.

    Read               Read a file

    Note: Depending on the user's access level, current conference and other
    BBS settings the commands may not be available, or they may work
    differently.

@EndNode

@Node UserCommands "UserCommands"

  User Commands
  =============

    Here's a list ofthe commands that can be used when you use the example
    configuration files are used, all these commands are completly
    configurable.

    Door Name          Details
    ================== =======================================================
    J                  Join Conference
    >                  Join Next Conference
    <                  Join Previous Conference
    RJ                 Re-Join a conference


    WHO                See WHO's On-line.
    WALL               Write Messages to users..
    STYLE              Change the style of ANSI
    CLS                Clears the screen
    X                  Change between beginner and expert mode
    S                  Display user's stats screen
    G                  Goodbye (Log Out)
    T                  Display the time
    LANGUAGE           Change your language
    LPS                Change the amount of lines per screen
    O                  Page the operator (sysop)
    SENT               Change your sentby information
    QS                 Quick stats
    W                  Edit your configuration

    E                  Write mail
    EC                 Write conference mail
    C                  Write a comment to the sysop
    R                  Read Mail
    MS                 MailScan, checks for mail to you in each conference.
    EMAIL              Write internet mail (*C* Not implemented in V1)

    U                  Upload files
    D                  Download files
    A                  Adjust list of tagged files
    F                  List files
    FR                 List files, newest first
    Z                  Search filelist
    ZFR                Search filelist, newest first.
    V                  View file
    N                  Display new files

    RL                 Re-login
    OLM                Send Online message to a user on another node
    NSTATS             Displays node statistics

    Note: Depending on the user's access level, current conference and other
    BBS settings the commands may not be available, or they may work
    differently.


@EndNode

